def: A porcelainlike kind of decorative pottery with a high gloss,which is sometimes iridescent. A very fine kind is made at Belleek inIreland.
Any aquatic lizard of the genus Varanus, as the monitor of theNile. See Monitor, n., 3.
Pertaining to, consisting chiefly or wholly of, dactyls; as,dactylic verses.
One of the parts which by their repetition make up a floweringplant, each being a single joint of a stem with its leaf or leaves; aphytomer.
Having the quality of leaning or inclining; as, the inclinatoryneedle.-- In*clin"a*to*ri*ly, adv. Sir T. Browne.
One who manufactures articles from wire.
To wed; to espouse. [Obs.]This markis hath her spoused with a ring. Chaucer.Though spoused, yet wanting wedlock's solemnize. Spenser.She was found again, and spoused to Marinell. Spenser.
Without a cloud; clear; bright.A cloudless winter sky. Bankroft.-- Cloud"less*ly, adv.-- Cloud"less*ness, n.
